t-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><h4 style="text-align: left;">Tinged with Philosophy</h4><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiTFTsKpjpDmU7KzpKbQVcjMVmMh-LD_LFCyjBIe_-wQF11qzA6ELhpwtzYPC2CIlHEmJuRBr3AnY8o54OaxkIURjMF_liCZ8DU2QFDmAwTlGTQh5j6Ntu3kqnJ7CAaOjM5OUgk9emgOpc/s900/p-1.jpg" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="635" data-original-width="900" height="452" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiTFTsKpjpDmU7KzpKbQVcjMVmMh-LD_LFCyjBIe_-wQF11qzA6ELhpwtzYPC2CIlHEmJuRBr3AnY8o54OaxkIURjMF_liCZ8DU2QFDmAwTlGTQh5j6Ntu3kqnJ7CAaOjM5OUgk9emgOpc/w640-h452/p-1.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br /><div>This comic strip invokes the moral philosophy, or lack thereof, of Niccolo Machiavelli who is famous for saying that rulers should not consider traditional ethical concerns, and instead focus on the maintenance of their power.</div><div><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEj51Z_e1a7c7UNZmoWPb96CjNoCK6RwZm_dttaStEU1AONl9BsBYvjmHgfz2TvXYZjD5iw8WQYGdFwo3_R2YOUFUEYDl7ES1jajXEDko9YXxVFyL084GjtysbwARJB7ptrZDl6wMrQqQgg/s1634/p-2.png" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="534" data-original-width="1634" height="210" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEj51Z_e1a7c7UNZmoWPb96CjNoCK6RwZm_dttaStEU1AONl9BsBYvjmHgfz2TvXYZjD5iw8WQYGdFwo3_R2YOUFUEYDl7ES1jajXEDko9YXxVFyL084GjtysbwARJB7ptrZDl6wMrQqQgg/w640-h210/p-2.png" width="640" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: left;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: left;">An open ended question.&nbsp;Is Calvin implying that nothing we do actually matters, or is he merely trying to help us understand their relative place in the universe?&nbsp;</div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: left;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhH2bAQXfHqnW1RtLt8vi2FVrAOSB90GvowLgTQP1GJ1ZE0WR2FjQPuDD0w1D8honh9k7U9glw2zHGffQdXU8i8Po99xM8L5wbRxhLC8o-kMkQJnY0ka_17SM0CCsw7cPNqXIWRg-0rZRY/s600/calvin-4.gif" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="415" data-original-width="600" height="442" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhH2bAQXfHqnW1RtLt8vi2FVrAOSB90GvowLgTQP1GJ1ZE0WR2FjQPuDD0w1D8honh9k7U9glw2zHGffQdXU8i8Po99xM8L5wbRxhLC8o-kMkQJnY0ka_17SM0CCsw7cPNqXIWRg-0rZRY/w640-h442/calvin-4.gif" width="640" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: left;">Natural morality.</div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: left;"><br /></div><br /><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><h4 style="text-align: left;">About education</h4><p></p><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjl6Nx1KuZ3P7AawAgHHUljHSfIjBlxNdwUOamNSDhD9AxScat11dQ9Bc2Bc8AMMj1VuW9amJC5VeeW_nqX7hNONY_jEB2kMDrqChIp0uX9fjdOV9k3EVwXXHqXNChUnHNQ0dv0hmFrYa4/s600/calvin-8.gif" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="189" data-original-width="600" height="202" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjl6Nx1KuZ3P7AawAgHHUljHSfIjBlxNdwUOamNSDhD9AxScat11dQ9Bc2Bc8AMMj1VuW9amJC5VeeW_nqX7hNONY_jEB2kMDrqChIp0uX9fjdOV9k3EVwXXHqXNChUnHNQ0dv0hmFrYa4/w640-h202/calvin-8.gif" width="640" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="h